e first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]},{"name":"Mared","meanings":["Simplified form of   Marged ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Marged verch Hywell was born in 1175, in Wales, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Cynwrig Fychan ap Cynwrig."},"et":{"1175–":"1175–Surnud","1174–Male":"1174–Surnud","1199–Male":"1199–Surnud","1175–Female":"1175–Surnud","ABT 1199":"umbes 1199","1199":"1199","1175":"1175","1174":"1174","of Clwyd,Wales":"Clwyd, Wales, United Kingdom","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1175–":"1175–Kuollut","1174–Male":"1174–Kuollut","1199–Male":"1199–Kuollut","1175–Female":"1175–Kuollut","ABT 1199":"noin 1199","1199":"1199","1175":"1175","1174":"1174","of Clwyd,Wales":"Clwyd, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1175–":"1175–Décédée","1174–Male":"1174–Décédé","1199–Male":"1199–Décédé","1175–Female":"1175–Décédée","ABT 1199":"environ 1199","1199":"1199","1175":"1175","1174":"1174","of Clwyd,Wales":"Clwyd, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","Wales, United Kingdom":"Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Marged verch Hywell est née en 1175, à Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Cynwrig Fychan ap Cynwrig."},"de":{"1175–":"1175–Verstorben","1174–Male":"1174–Verstorben","1199–Male":"1199–Verstorben","1175–